<br>
On the one hand, it looks excellent. It makes the whole game look a lot better. It's better organized, has many awesome new features like the pet window and contact list and is just all around cooler than the old one.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, I was literally getting like 3 frames per second. It was unreal. Worse than the worst raid lag with 150 corpses everywhere. And it wasn't because of too many people on test trying it out.<br>
<br>
At some point while struggling to zone out of rivervale (8 people in the zone btw) I hit alt-m and the &quot;action&quot; box went away. But guess what, so did my lag! <br>
<br>
Having that little main/action (the place where you click follow/sit/camp and put skills on buttons, etc) made the game BEYOND unplayable, it was absurd, but after removing it things were actual playable.<br>
<br>
Hitting alt-m again to bring it back returned me to unplayable framerate lag. Removing it again removed the lag again. <br>
<br>
Alt-O for options had the same effect. Certain other windows did also, to varying degress.<br>
<br>
I pray that when verant releases this they include an alternate &quot;low demands&quot; skin for it along with a way to turn off fading entirely, so that you can set all your transparencies once and not waste memory and cpu cycles on fading images every time you move your mouse. You can tell that they put a great deal of effort into it and it would be a shame for most people never to use it because it's just too darn laggy.<br>
